Samsung has unveiled the Notebook Odyssey Z at Intel’s launch event for new Intel Core i7 processors. The Samsung Notebook Odyssey Z sports a built-in Z AeroFlow cooling system, which consists of three key components: “They’re all built to keep the Odyssey Z cool in the heat of battle, whilst remaining lightweight and portable,” said Samsung. The Notebook Odyssey Z features an Nvidia GeForce GTX 1060 Max-P graphics card, an 8th-gen Intel Core i7 processor with 6 cores and 12 threads, and a 15.6-inch full HD display. The device also sports DDR4 RAM with a bandwidth of 2,400MHz, and a keyboard with Crater Keycaps delivering “enhanced precision and comfort”. The device will be available in selected countries in April, with US availability in Q3 2018.   